data.name: Savory Herb-Crusted Rack of Lamb
data.quickTastyDescription: A succulent rack of lamb coated in a fragrant herb crust, perfect for a special occasion or a delightful weekend dinner.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a small bowl, mix together the chopped rosemary, thyme, minced garlic, olive oil, salt, and pepper to create a herb paste.
Spread the herb paste evenly over the rack of lamb, pressing it into the meat.
Sprinkle the breadcrumbs over the herb paste, pressing lightly to adhere.
Place the rack of lamb in a roasting pan, bone side down, and roast in the preheated oven for about 25-30 minutes for medium-rare, or until it reaches your desired doneness.
Remove from the oven and let it rest for 10 minutes before slicing into individual chops.
